author: Inside Edition
description: Sabrina Carpenter spoke out after the White House used one of her songs in a video of ICE agents in action. "The video is evil and disgusting," the pop star posted on social media. "Do not ever involve me or my music to benefit your inhumane agenda."
title: Sabrina Carpenter Condemns White House For Using Song #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: Nearly 40 years after a Colorado mother was brutally raped and murdered, authorities say they finally know who is responsible. Rhonda Marie Fisher's body was found in Douglas County on April 1st, 1987. Despite extensive investigations, her killer was never found until this year when DNA from the scene matched serial killer Vincent Darrel Groves. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 1978 Cold Case Murder Of Rhonda Marie Fisher Solved In Colorado

author: Inside Edition
description: Therapy dogs are taking the fear and anxiety out of going to the dentist across the country. Softie, a labradoodle who works at Linden Dental Care in Beverly Hills, jumped on patient Nancy Meidel's lap to cuddle her during a procedure. A lab named Annie comforts patients in Colorado and a dog named Piper works at a dental office in Houston. The dogs are trained to follow specific commands. For example, "X-ray" is the dogs' cue to leave the room.
title: Therapy Dogs Are Helping Some Americans Ease Fear Of Going To Dentist

author: Inside Edition
description: After the Black Friday shooting at a mall in San Jose, California, hundreds ran for their lives. Some sought out shelter at a nearby home, where about 50 .strangers were welcomed by homeowners Martin and Irene Garcia. Inside Edition's Alison Hall got to speak to the Garcias.
title: Couple Sheltered Dozens Of Strangers After Black Friday Mall Shooting #shorts
